The palace was eerily calm and quiet as I waited for the key people whom I needed to support our reforms.

LineNo: 16417208,

Narrator: They were about to arrive to discus...
en


They were about to arrive to discuss the planned constitution that would democratize Rizia. A representative from each noble house was invited.

LineNo: 16417310,

Narrator: I shifted in my seat, scanning the...
en


I shifted in my seat, scanning the room as the invitees -- with Uncle Hugo at the front -- walked in.

LineNo: 16417892,

Narrator: On my gesture, everyone walked towa...
en


On my gesture, everyone walked toward their seats around the conference table.

LineNo: 16418010,

Player_Romus: Thank you for coming. I trust you...
en


"Thank you for coming. I trust you all received the draft and know exactly what we're doing here today."

LineNo: 16418118,

Player_Romus: I understand there has been some c...
en


"I understand there has been some concern about transferring my powers to the House of Delegates. Please, have a seat and let's discuss this like rational people."

LineNo: 16418220,

Player_Romus_Italic: They exchanged wary glances before...
en


They exchanged wary glances before taking their seats.

LineNo: 16418226,

Player_Romus_Italic: They exchanged wary glances before...
Menu Text en


Wait for them to get seated.

They exchanged wary glances before taking their seats.

LineNo: 16418494,

en


"We did..."

LineNo: 16418596,

Hugo Toras: Yes. We shall do that.
en


"Yes. We shall do that."

LineNo: 16418698,

Player_Romus: You all know why we're here. Our c...
en


"You all know why we're here. Our citizens have long been demanding democracy. It is my duty as the monarch to ensure that transition."

LineNo: 16418806,

Player_Romus: I know all of you have your own pe...
en


"I know all of you have your own personal opinions and concerns about this. This is the time for you to speak your minds -- each and every one of you. So we can settle this once and for all."

LineNo: 16418908,

Player_Romus: Very well. Let's begin. Shall we,...
en


"Very well. Let's begin. Shall we, Mr. Sazon?"

LineNo: 16419010,

Player_Romus: If we want our monarchy to survive...
en


"If we want our monarchy to survive this century -- we must adapt. Truly empowering the House and leaving the government to the people is the only way for our monarchy to survive."

LineNo: 16419118,

Player_Romus: We have gathered here to revolutio...
en


"We have gathered here to revolutionize Rizia and finally give the people of Rizia the right to rule themselves."

LineNo: 16419504,

Taddeus Azaro: I disagree, Your Majesty. It is no...
en


"I disagree, Your Majesty. It is not your duty at all."

LineNo: 16419606,

Rico Toras: That's not your duty, Your Majesty.
en


"That's not your duty, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 16419986,

Hugo Toras: Is that really your duty, Your Maj...
en


"Is that really your duty, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 16431490,

Taddeus Azaro: While I understand where you're co...
en


"While I understand where you're coming from, I do not agree with that sentiment, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 16431870,

en


"I will say right from the start that I have my doubts about such a radical proposal."

LineNo: 16431972,

Lucita Azaro: While I understand where you're co...
en


"While I understand where you're coming from, I must say that House Azaro does not agree with that sentiment."

en


"Very well."

Lucita Azaro: Very well.
en


"Very well."

en


"Very well."

en


"Very well."

LineNo: 16433316,

Manus Sazon: As you wish, Your Majesty.
en


"As you wish, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 16433418,

Manus Sazon: If I may...
en


"If I may..."

LineNo: 16433798,

Lucita Azaro: Is that really your duty, Your Maj...
en


"Is that really your duty, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 16433900,

Narrator: Manus cleared his throat and starte...
en


Manus cleared his throat and started speaking loudly, as if he was giving a speech in the House of Delegates.

LineNo: 16434002,

Manus Sazon: We are gathered here today because...
en


"We are gathered here today because the Rizian people have made their demands clear. If Rizia is going to ensure its prosperity, it must first ensure the freedom and the wellbeing of its citizens."

LineNo: 16434104,

Manus Sazon: This renewed and written constitut...
en


"This renewed and written constitution represents the will of Rizia -- not only those who have wealth and power, but the true spirit of the country."

LineNo: 16434206,

Manus Sazon: The changing times require us to a...
en


"The changing times require us to adapt. We already have a parliament and elections. Neither a single person nor a council of appointed nobles should dictate the will of a vast country like Rizia alone. And the fact is, His Majesty agrees."

LineNo: 16434308,

Manus Sazon: The monarchy will stay in place, a...
en


"The monarchy will stay in place, and the monarch will act as the head of state. But the true political power of the government will be left to the people, as it should be."

LineNo: 16434410,

Manus Sazon: We ask everyone to cooperate and s...
en


"We ask everyone to cooperate and support the implementation of this constitution."

LineNo: 16434790,

Hugo Toras: That's a lot to ask, isn't it?
en


"That's a lot to ask, isn't it?"

LineNo: 16436004,

Rico Toras: That's a lot to ask, isn't it?
en


"That's a lot to ask, isn't it?"

LineNo: 16436106,

Taddeus Azaro: With all due respect, I doubt that...
en


"With all due respect, I doubt that's going to work out."

LineNo: 16436208,

Lucita Azaro: With all due respect, I doubt that...
en


"With all due respect, I doubt that's going to work out."

LineNo: 16436310,

Angelica Sazon: You are starting to sound like you...
en


"You are starting to sound like your father, Manus. To a dangerous degree."

LineNo: 16436412,

Daria de Rava: I'll be honest. I'm also still dou...
en


"I'll be honest. I'm also still doubtful about all of this."

LineNo: 16436792,

Daria de Rava: As long as we can reach an agreeme...
en


"As long as we can reach an agreement, the RNC is ready to work with the RPP on this."

LineNo: 16438006,

Taddeus Azaro: Yes. It is.
en


"Yes. It is."

LineNo: 16438108,

Lucita Azaro: Yes. It is.
en


"Yes. It is."

LineNo: 16438210,

Angelica Sazon: I agree. You're starting to sound...
en


"I agree. You're starting to sound dangerously like your father, Manus."

LineNo: 16438312,

Daria de Rava: Yes. The RNC is also very doubtful...
en


"Yes. The RNC is also very doubtful about these drastic reforms."

LineNo: 16438414,

Daria de Rava: Well... As long as we can reach an...
en


"Well... As long as we can reach an agreement here today, the RNC is ready to work with the RPP on this."

LineNo: 16438612,

Manus Sazon: We understand the concerns. That i...
en


"We understand the concerns. That is the reason why I'm here today as the representative of the democratic movement. To show that this movement is not against the monarchy. To have dialogue and reach an agreement that involves everyone."

LineNo: 16438714,

Manus Sazon: That is great to hear.
en


"That is great to hear."

LineNo: 16438816,

Manus Sazon: His Majesty already supports the c...
en


"His Majesty already supports the constitution. He has granted you all the favor of inviting you here to provide your input."

LineNo: 16438918,

Manus Sazon: So... I would like to give the wor...
en


"So... I would like to give the word to King Romus."

LineNo: 16439020,

Narrator: I took a deep breath and looked aro...
en


I took a deep breath and looked around the table.

LineNo: 16439146,

Player_Romus: Mr. Sazon has said it all. We need...
en


"Mr. Sazon has said it all. We need to adapt. We already have a parliament and elected politicians. A single person cannot dictate the will of Rizia alone anymore."

LineNo: 16439254,

Player_Romus: First of all, I must point out tha...
en


"First of all, I must point out that we are not getting rid of the monarchy, nor the very institutions that hold our kingdom together. I will transfer our legislative powers to the parliament and executive powers to the head of government. I will remain the head of state."

LineNo: 16439640,

Player_Romus: Please take a look at what's happe...
en


"Please take a look at what's happening on the streets. People are discontent and they are organizing against our monarchy. The reality is clear as day."

LineNo: 16440018,

Player_Romus: Please take a look around. Million...
en


"Please take a look around. Millions are protesting and demanding democratic reforms. The reality is clear as day."

LineNo: 16440126,

Player_Romus: When I acceded to the throne, I pr...
en


"When I acceded to the throne, I promised to focus on reforming this country. The time for that transformation has finally come."

LineNo: 16440512,

Player_Romus: When I took the throne, I had no i...
en


"When I took the throne, I had no intention of ceding any of my power. However, I am now convinced that I have a responsibility towards the Rizian people. And this transformation is necessary to adapt to the coming century."

LineNo: 16441288,

Player_Romus: We cannot ignore the will of the p...
en


"We cannot ignore the will of the people. And I am definitely not going to repeat the mistakes of my father."

LineNo: 16441396,

Player_Romus: We cannot ignore the unrest, nor c...
en


"We cannot ignore the unrest, nor can we silence every voice that is raised against us. I am definitely not going to repeat the mistakes of my father."

LineNo: 16441504,

Player_Romus: I don't want to go down in history...
en


"I don't want to go down in history as another monarch who tried to desperately cling to power. It is my duty to ensure this transition is smooth and peaceful."

LineNo: 16441612,

Player_Romus: As the monarch, I have the power t...
en


"As the monarch, I have the power to ensure a peaceful transition by listening to the people and I intend to use it. We all know what happened during the Century of Revolutions."

LineNo: 16441720,

Player_Romus: I believe in incremental change, n...
en


"I believe in incremental change, not radical transformation. These reforms are merely a continuation of what my father accomplished. All of you will be able to carry on much as before."

LineNo: 16441940,

Player_Romus: Our hands are forced, and frankly,...
en


"Our hands are forced, and frankly, it's time we listen. As unfortunate it is, this is in the best interests of all of us."

LineNo: 16442326,

Player_Romus: Our system is inefficient. Absolut...
en


"Our system is inefficient. Absolute rule within the hands of a few cannot manage the intricacies of the 20th century."

LineNo: 16442434,

Player_Romus: Just because we are born into nobi...
en


"Just because we are born into nobility doesn't mean we have to fight to protect our privileges. Rizia must slowly transform into a democracy."

LineNo: 16442542,

Player_Romus: Let's be honest. We all would pref...
en


"Let's be honest. We all would prefer to keep our massive wealth and our prestige as opposed to risking our heads trying to secure our political power, wouldn't we? Why even fight?"

LineNo: 16442650,

Player_Romus: Let's be honest. Would you prefer...
en


"Let's be honest. Would you prefer to keep your heads and your already accumulated wealth as a noble family, or would you rather lose both?"

LineNo: 16443704,

Narrator: General Taddeus grunted in disappro...
en


General Taddeus grunted in disapproval.

Narrator: Lucita Azaro frowned in disapproval...
en


Lucita Azaro frowned in disapproval.

en


Daria de Rava tutted in disapproval.

en


Angelica Sazon clicked her tongue in disapproval.

LineNo: 16444668,

en


Uncle Hugo frowned in disapproval.

LineNo: 16444770,

Narrator: Uncle Hugo nodded approvingly.
en


Uncle Hugo nodded approvingly.

LineNo: 16444872,

Player_Romus: If we join forces together, we can...
en


"If we join forces together, we can display the world our unity and resilience. We have a choice to make, and according to it, we will go down in history as heroes or villains."

LineNo: 16444980,

Player_Romus: Don't stand against change. Be a p...
en


"Don't stand against change. Be a part of it. I am asking you as your King."

Narrator: They listened to me with no express...

They listened to me with no expression on their faces.

"Yes. Let's do that."

LineNo: 16448654,

Player_Romus: We are abolishing the Royal Counci...
en


"We are abolishing the Royal Council and will transfer the power to form a cabinet of ministers to the head of government."

LineNo: 16448762,

Player_Romus: There will no longer be appointed...
en


"There will no longer be appointed nobles who can exercise executive powers. The government will be formed by the people, for the people."

LineNo: 16448870,

Player_Romus: Yes. The council will be abolished...
en


"Yes. The council will be abolished. Instead the new head of government, the Prime Minister, will form a cabinet and lead the ministers."

LineNo: 16448978,

Player_Romus: We will also centralize Rizia's re...
en


"We will also centralize Rizia's regional structure and abolish the semi-autonomy of each province."

LineNo: 16449086,

Player_Romus: I know you may not be fond of the...
en


"I know you may not be fond of the centralization point. But it is a necessity to ensure the new government can exercise its powers efficiently and equally all across Rizia."

LineNo: 16449194,

Player_Romus: The Houses will no longer enjoy en...
en


"The Houses will no longer enjoy enormous authority and privileges in their respective provinces. We will abolish the autonomous structure and centralize the system in Porte Drazon."

LineNo: 16449866,

Hugo Toras: Concerning...
en


"Concerning..."

LineNo: 16451080,

Rico Toras: I can't believe this point is up f...
en


"I can't believe this point is up for discussion."

en


"Outrageous..."

LineNo: 16451284,

Lucita Azaro: Unbelievable...
en


"Unbelievable..."

en


"Too much, Your Majesty. Just too much."

LineNo: 16451696,

Player_Romus: I will remain the head of state an...
en


"I will remain the head of state and represent our kingdom in the international arena and protect our royal traditions."

LineNo: 16451804,

Player_Romus: As the monarch, I will retain the...
en


"As the monarch, I will retain the final say over any legislation in order to protect the integrity of our kingdom."

LineNo: 16452190,

Player_Romus: I will reign as a symbolic monarch...
en


"I will reign as a symbolic monarch only. The parliament of this country will have the final say in legislature."

LineNo: 16452298,

Player_Romus: The legislative branch will freely...
en


"The legislative branch will freely represent the people and take actions accordingly within the scope of the constitution."

LineNo: 16452788,

Player_Romus: We will form an upper house consis...
en


"We will form an upper house consisting of the nobility. Each of the Houses will continue to be represented there in the legislative branch."

LineNo: 16453476,

Player_Romus: The nobility will be represented i...
en


"The nobility will be represented in the House of Lords, and will act as a balance to the lower house. Any legislation would require both houses to come to an agreement."

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the nobility will be given an equal voice with the establishment of an upper house."

LineNo: 16453692,

Player_Romus: The nobility will be represented i...
en


"The nobility will be represented in the House of Lords and will act as a balance to the lower house. Any constitutional or structural changes will require the agreement of the upper house."

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the nobility will be given a voice with the establishment of an upper house, retaining limited say over the legislative branch."

LineNo: 16453908,

Player_Romus: The nobility will be represented i...
en


"The nobility will be represented in the House of Lords and will act as an advisory body to the lower house."

LineNo: 16454016,

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the nobility will be given an advisory role with the establishment of an upper house."

LineNo: 16454124,

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the provinces will be given a voice with the establishment of an upper house, retaining a significant say in government."

LineNo: 16454232,

Player_Romus: We will form an upper house consis...
en


"We will form an upper house consisting of regional representatives from regions to create a bicameral legislature."

LineNo: 16454920,

Player_Romus: The regions will be represented in...
en


"The regions will be represented in the Senate  and will act as a balance to the lower house. Any legislation would require both houses to come to an agreement."

LineNo: 16455028,

Player_Romus: The provinces will be represented...
en


"The provinces will be represented in parliament and will act as a balance to the lower house. Any constitutional or structural changes will require the agreement of the upper house."

LineNo: 16455136,

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the provinces will be given a voice with the establishment of an upper house, retaining a limited say in government."

LineNo: 16455244,

Player_Romus: The regions will be represented in...
en


"The regions will be represented in the Senate and will act as an advisory body to the lower house."

LineNo: 16455352,

Player_Romus: As a compromise, the legislative b...
en


"As a compromise, the legislative branch will be divided into two and the regions will be given an advisory role with the establishment of an upper house."

General Taddeus let out a sarcastic laugh.

Uncle Hugo crossed his arms.

en


"Interesting..."

Player_Romus: We'll also form a Supreme Court th...
en


"We'll also form a Supreme Court that will provide the necessary checks and balances to the legislative and the executive branches."

LineNo: 16458986,

Player_Romus: And the judicial branch will ensur...
en


"And the judicial branch will ensure that the constitution is being followed by the other branches of government."

LineNo: 16459094,

Player_Romus: We'll form a Supreme Court, and we...
en


"We'll form a Supreme Court, and we will give the justices immunity so that they cannot be threatened by powerful interests or the acting executive."

LineNo: 16459202,

en


"We'll form the Supreme Court and we will grant them life tenure, which would free them from the pressure of protecting powerful interests or making decisions according to momentary populism."

LineNo: 16459304,

Player_Romus: We will form a Supreme Court. Just...
en


"We will form a Supreme Court. Justices will be granted he power of judicial review and to declare laws unconstitutional, so that they can keep the legislative and the executive branches in check."

LineNo: 16459406,

Player_Romus: We will form a Supreme Court. I wi...
en


"We will form a Supreme Court. I will retain control over their composition, so that the monarchy can keep the legislative and the executive branches in check."

Player_Romus: And as for the new government, I w...
en


"And as for the new government, I will appoint a transitionary Prime Minister to oversee the implementation of the reforms until the next elections."

Player_Romus: And as for the head of government,...
en


"And as for the head of government, I will appoint Manus Sazon, the elected leader of the House."

"And as for the head of government, I will appoint Manus Sazon, the leader of the RPP. He and the RPP must be in charge of the transition."

"As a compromise, I'd like to appoint Daria de Rava as the head of government to oversee the transition."

"And as for the head of government, I will appoint Daria de Rava, the elected leader of the House."

"And who would that be?"

"Your Majesty..."

"I am supportive of your plans and the new constitution."

"I will appoint Manus Sazon, of course. He is the elected leader of the House."

"As a compromise, I'd like to appoint Daria de Rava as the head of government to oversee the transition."

He sighed.
